reviewText: The Jimmy Buffett DVD - Live At Wrigley Field does not disappoint.  It has very good sound and vision quality and Jimmy and the band are in top form and so are the audience of loyal parrot heads.The chosen song list is very good with two versions of City Of New Orleans. One as a duet with Mac McAnally and one on the extras with the full band a stand out of the show.This DVD is about as close as we in Australia are likely to get to see Jimmy Buffett live as to my knowledge he has never toured here.
summary: Aussie Tony reviews Jimmy Buffett DVD

reviewText: I'm sure all of you huge Jimmy Buffett fans out there are wondering why I would rate this live concert only 2 Stars?  And why I would call it "a major disappointment"?Because it IS a major disappointment!  I am displeased with the poor sound quality of the performance.  I am shocked that his shows are more about engaging his "drunk and crazy audience", than they are about his wonderful music.Jimmy Buffett is one of my all time favorite recording artists.  His ballads about life and traveling souls (like myself) hit home with me, in song after song after song.  However, when you watch him perform these same songs live on this DVD...they lose everything (in my opinion).He just "mails them in" with the exception of "A Pirate Looks at Forty".  Its the only ballad of that entire show where he sounded as though he was trying hard to sing it serious and make it sound perfect.  Compare Jimmy's lackadasical style to the Eagle's live shows?  And there is no comparison.  I if wanted to get drunk I don't need to be surrounded by 50,000 other drunks...while trying to listen to my favorite Jimmy Buffett songs!I traded back in my DVD of this show and took a loss on it.  I also will never attend one of his live shows after watching this DVD.  However, I will continue to listen to my 12+ CD collection of Jimmy Buffett recordings I've collected over the many years of his career.  His music is wonderful...but his live DVD show was a "major disappointment"!

reviewText: The magic of a Buffett concert has finally after all these years of waiting has arrived....and my oh my was it worth the wait...For those of us in the know a Jimmy Buffett concert is pure magic... a 3 hour (or more depending on how long you tailgated lol) concert of incredible musicianship and a mini vacation from all the troubles of the world....now we can have this magic when ever we need it 24-7-365 and the way the world is going lord knows we need it...The music unites us as a people to have fun and to laugh and to remember at the same time....For those who dont know or who have never have had the "experience" now is the time to find out what the rest of us know..the Joy the happiness the TALENT the fun of a JB concert...The magic of Jimmy and his band that he can take us to the islands and back but he attracts the young, the old and  everyone in between and spans races and we all come together as ONE as a people to celebrate the JOY of music....and in these trying times we should all be thankful for bands like the coral reefer band....and if this music does not move you then you TRUELY ARE DEAD.....DO NOT MISS THIS MISS THIS...a truly wonderful night of music GARUENTEED to lift your spirits.....As for the music all the hits are there every thing you could want...the band is SPOT on (as always...although I must admit I do miss "Fingers") and the sound and the dvd is supurb in every way the only thing i would have changed is Putting the Star Spangeled Banner at the Beginning Of the Concert not as bonus material...but none the less this is PURE JOY!!!!!
summary: Rejoyce Parrotheads for it has ARRIVED

reviewText: Concert DVD's like this are often compilations of numerous shows. You get to see songs performed live but miss out on the stuff between songs.This is a nice continuous video of the entire show at Wrigley Field. You get various camera angles so it doesn't get boring. And you get all teh banter in between songs with Jimmy introducing the band and telling stories and all that stuff you see at any live mucis show. This really immerses you into the show and makes you feel like you were actually there.

reviewText: The concert isn't as long as I thought it was, by the look of the dvd, it looks like it runs approximatly 2 hours and 45 minutes. But it abou 2 hours and 15 minutes, that counts both shows that are seen on this dvd, the first one being about a hour long, and the 2nd one, about 75 minutes long, but here you do the math. I didn't think any of the concert was recored, expect for what you saw on the local news, but I am glad they finnaly brought it out on dvd, and they didn't even play the show on TV. The first disc has songs from Act I of the afternoon show that was recored on Labor Day of 05, and disc 2 is the show that did the night before. So you might be disappointed that act II of the afternoon show is not on the dvd. After the first 2 songs on disc 1, Jimmy Buffet takes off his home white Chicago Cubs uniform that he has on, don't worry he has another shirt on underneath, and autographes it, and annouces that it will be sold on e-bay. The songs in the concert on disc one are Piece of work, The Pascagoula run, Hey good lookin', Changes in Latitudes, changes in attitudes, I will play for Gumbo, Come Monday, Last mango in Paris, Woman goin' crazy on Carloine street, License to chill, Son of a son of a sailor, Cheeseburger in paradise, Volcano, and Brown Eted Girl. The songs in the concert on disc 2 are Why don't we get drunk, La vie dansante, Banana republics, Southern cross, School boy heart, A pirate looks at Forty, The City, It's 5 o'clock somewhere, One paricular harbour, Margaritaville, Fins, Scarlet begonias, and City of New Orleans. The 2nd disc actally begins with the late Steve Goodman singing Go Cubs Go. And in between A pirate looks Forty and The city, Jimmy Buffet is seen singing Take me out to the ballgame in the Cubs' TV booth. The people that are stage are, starting with the vocals and guitar are Jimmy Buffet, Peter Mayer, Jim, Mayer on bass guitar and vocals and  Mac McAnally. And now for the Coral Reffer Band, Michael Utley on keyboards, Robert Greenbridge on steel drums and timbales, Ralph MacDonald on percussion, Roger Guth on drums, Doyle Grishman on pedal steel guitar, Amy Lee and Tom Mitchell on saxophone, John Lovell on Trumpet, and special guest on keyboards Bill Payne. The vocalists are Nadirah Shakoor, and Tina Gullickson, and finnaly the dancers are Heather Perry and Louisa Kendrick. Before Labor Day weekend of 05, Wrigley Field was only used from sports games, but mainly for Chicago Cubs home games. So Jimmy Buffet becomes the first singer/musican to use Wrigley Field for a concert venue, and hey if they did it once, they can do it again.

reviewText: Because the samples of this DVD on Buffett's website sound horrible, and because his prior concert DVD has received only bad reviews, I was really worried about what this DVD would look and sound like.But my fears were unfounded.  Except for a few pre-show crowd shots, this DVD looks and sounds amazing!  And you have your choice of stereo or 5.1 surround sound.  This DVD is like being at a live Buffett concert!  In fact, it is better because his concerts sell out so quickly I have never had any hope of getting front row seats to any of his concerts!  I finally know what I have been missing!After years of waiting, Buffett fans finally have the concert DVD they deserve!  I usually hate concert DVDs, but I can't recommend this DVD enough to established fans of Buffett's music or people who want to experience one of his concerts for the first time!
